{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Safeguard registered charities from disruptive protests including buffer zones",
        "additional_details": "Many registered charities are attended by vulnerable individuals and are often located in residential and commercial areas, where loud noise can disrupt local residents and businesses.\r\n \r\nThere have been instances of protestors using loudspeakers, shouting, and offensive or sexually explicit language, causing distress and disturbance.\r\nWe call on the Government to introduce targeted measures, such as buffer zones, to prevent protests in the vicinity of these registered charity premises.",
        "background": "We ask the UK Government to introduce proportionate safeguards to protect premises operated by charities registered with the Charity Commission from disruptive and abusive protests.",
